    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.26.40a" />
                <note type="curatorial">88-1 Aly Collection</note>
                
                
                
                <opener>
                <dateline>12-7-'59 </dateline>
                
                
                <salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I've just heard that Rex Carey died a day or so ago. My last letter to him arrived just before or just after his going. I hope it arrived just <hi rend="underline">before</hi>, because in that letter I told <del/> him that he was dear to me. I've written his wife. Old Rex sent me <del/><add>two</add> letters I wrote
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.26.40b"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                    
                    him 50 years ago!! He cherished them all those years. I aim to send them on to you, and will soon.</p>
                
                <p>I still dislike you and your family.(*)</p>
                <closer>
                <signed>John</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript><opener>*</opener> <p><hi rend="underline">The very idea!</hi> Who <hi rend="underline">ever</hi> said that? I <hi rend="underline">do too</hi> like all of you, bless your hearts!</p></postscript>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">40</fw>
            </div1>
        </body>
        
